Module: vionet.sys — virtio-net NDIS 3.0 miniport driver. Sits on
top of ndis.sys and our shared virtio.lib. tcpip.sys binds to it
automatically once both ndis.sys + tcpip.sys are loaded.

PCI device: virtio-net-pci, vendor 0x1AF4 device 0x1041 (modern) /
0x1000 (transitional). QEMU exposes it via:
    -netdev user,id=n0 -device virtio-net-pci,netdev=n0

Two virtqueues only: rxq (device->driver, queue 0) and txq
(driver->device, queue 1). Modern features negotiated:
    VIRTIO_F_VERSION_1
    VIRTIO_NET_F_MAC      (read MAC from device config)
    VIRTIO_NET_F_STATUS   (read link state from device config)

Explicitly NOT negotiated: MRG_RXBUF, GUEST_CSUM, GUEST_TSO*,
CTRL_VQ. Keeps the driver simple; we accept the cost of one buffer
per RX'd frame.

!ENDIF

MAJORCOMP=ntos
MINORCOMP=ndis

TARGETNAME=vionet
TARGETPATH=$(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib
TARGETTYPE=DRIVER

INCLUDES=..\..\inc;..\..\virtio\inc

TARGETLIBS=$(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib\*\ndis.lib    \
           $(BASEDIR)\public\sdk\lib\*\virtio.lib

C_DEFINES=-DNDIS_MINIPORT_DRIVER -DBINARY_COMPATIBLE=0

SOURCES=vionet.c \
        vionet.rc
